<div id="rules">

    <h2>Squirrel Rules</h2>


    <p>
        These are the rules I use for Squirrel. I got them from a website <a href="http://cyclowiki.org/wiki/%D0%91%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%BA%D0%B0_(%D0%BA%D0%B0%D1%80%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%87%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%8F_%D0%B8%D0%B3%D1%80%D0%B0)" target="_blank">pagat.com</a>. 
    </p>

    <h3>Genearal Description</h3>
    <p>
        Squirrel is a four-player card game played among residents of Kazakhstan (a team game consists of 2 people). The goal is to win the game in one of two ways:

        Gain 12 or more points (eyes) in the game;
        score 120 points in the distribution (Such a victory is called «Golaya») if the players wish the current game can be continued, considering that the team has won one game.
        The game consists of several games called hand-outs. The game is played with a 36-card deck
    </p>

    <h3>Value of Cards</h3>
    <p>
        There are cards in the deck that have unique values, that are:

        Ace - 11 points;
        Ten to ten points;
        King - 4 points
        Queen - 3 points;
        Jack - 2 points;
        Cards that have no points and differ from each other are: Sevens, Eights and Niners In a deck of 120 points

    </p>

    <h3>The Trump</h3>
    <p>
        In the game there are 2 types of trumps, permanent trumps (Jacks) and temporary (assigned for the time of the hand-out). Permanent trumps are jacks, they go by seniority according to this order: hearts, diamonds, clubs, and spades. The strongest Jack of the Clubs, he beats any card (including the other Jacks and the trump shape), followed by the Jack of Spades, he beats everything but the Jack of the Clubs and so on, the weakest of the Jacks is the Jack of Diamonds. The assigned trump is a bargaining chip, which is assigned after the cards are dealt, and is assigned by the player with whom the Jack of the Clubs is held. In the first game, whoever gets the Jack of the Clubs is the bearer of the card of the Clubs for the whole game, the other trumps are assigned as follows: his teammate gets the trump of the Spades, the player of the other team, sitting from him on the left hand of the Hearts, and the player on the right of the Diamonds. Over the course of the following hand-outs, the player who received the Jack of the Clubs at the hand announces the bargaining chip that he received during the distribution of the cards during his first horse.
    </p>

    <h3>Role of Sixes</h3>
    <p>
        Sixes are used for «record» points. Each pair of players gets 2 sixes. One puts the shirt down, the other six covers it with the shirt up. When the pair wins 1 point, it opens with the top card of the so-called 1 «eye» at the bottom six (a small image of the suit on the card itself). When all six eyes are open, the top six is turned down by the shirt and the score is already 6 to 12.
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>Dealing</strong> The first distributor is determined by drawing lots or otherwise. In the next game, the next player deals to the left of the previous distributor. The deck is carefully shuffled, then shifted by the player to the left of the dealer and each player is given 8 cards two cards at a time. The player that shifts the cards has the right to «trust» the distributor and tap cards instead of shifting, in this case each is given 8 cards at once. In the first batch, the trump shape is always the clubs.
    </p>
    <h4>Gameplay</h4>
    <p>
        Each player is given 8 cards (or 7 depending on the parameter, without sevens). The first move is made by a person positioned on the left hand of the giver. The main rule, players have to put the suit in which entered, if the player does not have such, he has the right to put a trump («chop» card) or any other suit («leak» card), the one whose card is older and takes these 4 cards «bribe» and gets the right to make the next move. There’s a nuance, you can’t throw an ace on another suit if you haven’t worn it before. The goal of the team is to take as many bribes as possible and score points, score more points and win the hand.
    </p>

    <h5>Counting points</h5>
    <p>
        The order of the opening of the eyes at the end of the hand is as follows:

        1 eye - if the team scored more than 60 points and in the course of handing out the trump was from this team;
        2 eyes - if the team scored more than 60 points and in the course of handing out the trump was from the team of the rival.



        There is also a 30-point mark, which is called «saved» and if one of the teams scores less than 30 points, then the winning team opens 1 eye more. In the first round, the winning team opens two eyes anyway. If both teams have scored 60 points (eggs), then in this case the game continues and in this handout the eyes are not opened, the winning team opens the next number of eyes (Depends on previously agreed rules)4 eyes or number of eyes open in the second batch multiplied by 2.
    </p>




